HEADWORD: Suberone
<hw>Su"ber*one</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The hypothetical ketone of suberic acid.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A colorless liquid, analogous suberone proper, having
a pleasant peppermint odor. It is obtained by the distillation of
calcium suberate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

